France, Germany Plan Second Summit to Plan ‘Ambitious’ Debt-Crisis Package

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-10-20T17:18:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/france-germany-plan-second-summit-to-plan-ambitious-debt-crisis-package.html
German Chancellor  Angela Merkel  and
French President Nicolas Sarkozy have agreed to ask euro-region
leaders to assess a “comprehensive and ambitious” package of
measures to solve the region’s debt crisis at a leaders’ summit
on Oct. 23 in order to agree on the measures at a second meeting
by Oct. 26 at the latest, German government spokesman Steffen
Seibert said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rainer Buergin at 
 rbuergin1@bloomberg.net  